Span.Text: In-vehicle and hand-held mobile devices, enabled with apps and cloud services, help first responders to gather and upload information digitally (e.g., images, video, and audio files) to provide a first-hand perspective from the scene of an event or emergency. With security-enhanced mobile connections to the agency network or command centre, the digital files can be quickly reviewed to help improve citizen safety and agency response.

Automating officer tasks to reduce reliance on people and share the responsibility, (no thought process, it just happens).  As soon as you step outside a boundary the paperwork is prepared for CPS immediately in workflow.  Location based information means less time spent telling everyone about everything.  Wherever the officers are they're much more aware of what's going on around them.
The Events Dashboard shows events relevant to your current location.  Updates are provided on a regular basis.
A map view provides instant visual access to your location and the incidents around you.  You can drill into any incident to find out more information.
A custody reference is entered to which the evidence will be linked.
